    "comment": "Rationale: DGKI was localized in cell bodies, dendrites, dendritic spines, and axon terminals.\n\n26/01/2018 Pim\nAuthors state:\n- \"In the cerebellar Purkinje and molecular layers, DGKι signals were detected in cell bodies, dendritic spines, and axon terminals (Figure 3E-G). \"\n- \"Quantitative analysis indicated that DGKι signals are present in 13.3±2.5% of axon terminals and 44.2±4.0% of dendritic spines in the hippocampal CA1 region (n=3 animals for wild type (WT) and knockout (KO); total area analysed, 232.2 μm2/animal). \". Experimental description: Materials and methods\nAnimals\nSprague-Dawley rats (280-300 g) were used for rat neuron culture, in vivo coimmunoprecipitation, immunoblot analysis, and electron microscopy.",
